<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="88" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,892,1891]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,356,1576,1602]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The species epithet “labrisicus” refers to the shape of the central area resembling a “ 
<emphasis box="[1325,1395,1576,1602]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">labrys</emphasis>
” – a double-headed axe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="88" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,892,1891]" box="[189,860,1648,1675]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,373,1648,1674]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Distribution:—</emphasis>
